hes review-safe Agent Trails.\n\nThe server side of the Agent Trail application is expected to use the\n`but-agentlog` crate to interact with captured data. It should call\n`but-agentlog` read/query/projection primitives rather than reimplementing\nGitMeta key parsing, transcript normalization, target verification, or bounded\nrecord hydration.\n\nToday `but-agentlog` is mostly CLI-shaped. The Agent Trail MVP may need a small\npublic library API for server use. Prefer adding that API over shelling out to\n`but agentlog` from Forge.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:05:11.729Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}